title: Lamamra received Deputy Minister of Foreign Affairs of Thailand
text: Minister of Foreign Affairs and National Community Abroad, Ramtane Lamamra, received, Thursday, Deputy Minister of Foreign Affairs of Thailand, Vijavat Isarabhakd, who is on a working visit to Algeria, where he signed a memorandum of understanding on political consultations between the two countries.

Welcoming the importance of this agreement in strengthening bilateral relations, consultation and coordination between the two countries, Lamamra stressed the need to double efforts to extend cooperation between Algeria and Thailand to other areas, such as agriculture, energy and tourism.

For his part, Deputy Foreign Minister of Thailand welcomed the level of political relations between the two countries, expressing his satisfaction with the successful results of his visit to Algeria which will open promising prospects for relations between the two countries.
